                  </hi>. I keep a shop at Uxbridge. On the 20th of March, the prisoner came, and bought a 1/4 <hi rend="italic">lb.</hi> of cooked meat—when he went out, I missed 2 1/2 <hi rend="italic">b.</hi> of bacon—I went out and found him about five yards from the shop, in the act of putting it down on the ground—I gave him in charge—I knew him before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Have I not always paid my way, and borne a good cha racter? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I am sorry to say very different—he came to my shop every night, and I generally lost bacon—he used to watch me out.</p>
